1
00:00:20,680 --> 00:00:23,320
♪The wind blows through her curly hair♪

2
00:00:23,320 --> 00:00:25,560
♪And her sweet cheeks♪

3
00:00:27,040 --> 00:00:29,720
♪She accepts youth as a cryptic syntax♪

4
00:00:29,720 --> 00:00:32,050
♪And expresses it with sincerity♪

5
00:00:32,490 --> 00:00:38,430
♪Growing up, she's a stubborn flower♪

6
00:00:38,890 --> 00:00:44,930
♪Was she afraid?
She once asked herself that too♪

7
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:51,690
♪Hypatia, that passionate version of her♪

8
00:00:51,690 --> 00:00:57,740
♪Dazzling like midsummer, melting sorrow♪

9
00:00:58,050 --> 00:01:04,470
♪Hypatia, that radiant version of her♪

10
00:01:04,470 --> 00:01:10,710
♪If love is complicated,
she answers with a smile♪

11
00:01:34,220 --> 00:01:35,800
=Love Formula=
(Adapted from Jin Xiamei's novel)

12
00:01:35,801 --> 00:01:37,380
=Love Formula=
("Devil Young Master, Don't Mess With Me" )

13
00:01:37,540 --> 00:01:40,820
=Episode 3=

14
00:01:56,374 --> 00:01:57,460
Han Yansheng?

15
00:01:57,780 --> 00:01:59,060
I knew it was you.

16
00:01:59,757 --> 00:02:01,060
What are you doing here?

17
00:02:01,258 --> 00:02:02,620
Don't play dumb.

18
00:02:04,300 --> 00:02:05,860
What's with the attitude?

19
00:02:06,444 --> 00:02:08,777
Do you think I wanted to come
to this concert with you?

20
00:02:15,133 --> 00:02:17,140
Just leave if you want to.
Don't block the view.

21
00:02:17,177 --> 00:02:19,280
Right. Don't come
if you're unable to appreciate it.

22
00:02:19,288 --> 00:02:21,088
What's the point of coming up
just to leave?

23
00:02:24,420 --> 00:02:25,860
The performance has already started.

24
00:02:25,980 --> 00:02:26,860
If you leave now,

25
00:02:27,133 --> 00:02:28,380
you'll just disturb everyone.

26
00:02:28,660 --> 00:02:30,300
It's also disrespectful
to the musicians.

27
00:03:45,620 --> 00:03:46,380
Still here?

28
00:03:48,900 --> 00:03:51,020
For you to fall asleep
at such a classy concert,

29
00:03:51,140 --> 00:03:53,860
what a waste of something so precious.

30
00:03:54,740 --> 00:03:56,439
I wouldn't be this exhausted

31
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:58,090
if you didn't constantly
order me around.

32
00:03:59,740 --> 00:04:01,740
Why didn't you wake me

33
00:04:01,740 --> 00:04:02,780
when the concert ended?

34
00:04:05,700 --> 00:04:07,940
She's exhausted.
Let her sleep a little longer.

35
00:04:08,180 --> 00:04:10,420
You can wake her
after you're done cleaning up.

36
00:04:19,020 --> 00:04:20,100
Do I know you that well?

37
00:04:22,060 --> 00:04:24,980
Glad to hear you say that. See you.

38
00:04:26,604 --> 00:04:27,180
Wait.

39
00:04:28,477 --> 00:04:30,152
Where did you get that bike?

40
00:04:32,020 --> 00:04:32,900
Over there.

41
00:04:34,980 --> 00:04:36,300
But tough luck.

42
00:04:36,660 --> 00:04:37,460
It's the last one.

43
00:04:41,980 --> 00:04:43,700
Just my luck.

44
00:04:47,140 --> 00:04:49,260
Seeing how miserable you look,

45
00:04:49,900 --> 00:04:51,020
I'll give you a ride.

46
00:04:52,020 --> 00:04:52,580
Hop on.

47
00:04:55,170 --> 00:04:56,288
I don't need your pity.

48
00:04:59,300 --> 00:05:00,420
Suit yourself.

49
00:05:05,696 --> 00:05:06,860
Last chance,

50
00:05:06,933 --> 00:05:07,860
are you coming or not?

51
00:05:09,220 --> 00:05:10,540
I'd rather walk until sunrise

52
00:05:10,934 --> 00:05:13,020
than get on that bike with you.

53
00:05:18,980 --> 00:05:20,660
Slow down! You're going too fast!

54
00:05:21,616 --> 00:05:22,576
You dress like a lady.

55
00:05:22,640 --> 00:05:23,777
But behaves like a tomboy.

56
00:05:24,760 --> 00:05:26,111
You're doing this on purpose!

57
00:05:27,860 --> 00:05:28,900
Jian Dan, listen.

58
00:05:29,066 --> 00:05:30,933
What happened today stays between us!

59
00:05:30,955 --> 00:05:32,622
Don't tell anyone at school.

60
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:34,331
I'll think about it.

61
00:05:34,350 --> 00:05:35,500
What's there to think about?

62
00:05:35,743 --> 00:05:37,020
Helmet. Give me the helmet!

63
00:05:37,220 --> 00:05:38,380
Slow down! Watch it!

64
00:05:38,420 --> 00:05:39,220
Speed bump ahead!

65
00:05:39,272 --> 00:05:39,940
Hey, slow down!

66
00:05:43,860 --> 00:05:47,900
Okay, easy. Easy...

67
00:05:56,460 --> 00:05:57,860
That wasn't exactly a fun ride.

68
00:05:58,420 --> 00:06:00,088
But thank you for giving me a ride.

69
00:06:03,860 --> 00:06:05,780
Don't give me concert tickets
ever again.

70
00:06:06,220 --> 00:06:07,540
Your scholarship

71
00:06:07,620 --> 00:06:08,940
is for studying.

72
00:06:09,133 --> 00:06:10,511
Even if you give me another one,

73
00:06:10,860 --> 00:06:11,860
I won't go.

74
00:06:14,860 --> 00:06:18,340
When did I give you a ticket?

75
00:06:18,900 --> 00:06:20,288
Drop the act.

76
00:06:20,780 --> 00:06:22,703
I found it under the photo frame,

77
00:06:22,731 --> 00:06:24,020
next to the broken trophy.

78
00:06:24,120 --> 00:06:25,711
And we were sitting next to each other.

79
00:06:25,900 --> 00:06:27,820
So, who else could have put it there?

80
00:06:28,780 --> 00:06:29,580
Jian Dan.

81
00:06:29,940 --> 00:06:32,620
This is for tonight's 8 PM concert.

82
00:06:32,940 --> 00:06:34,420
Take a moment to relax

83
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:35,555
and clear your head.

84
00:06:35,922 --> 00:06:37,260
I didn't earn this.

85
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:38,940
Besides, that ticket is expensive.

86
00:06:39,020 --> 00:06:40,500
You should go.

87
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,900
We're classmates and roommates.

88
00:06:43,423 --> 00:06:44,820
If you don't take it,

89
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:47,311
it means you're still mad
about the hair dye thing.

90
00:06:48,660 --> 00:06:49,900
Jian Dan, just take it.

91
00:06:49,980 --> 00:06:51,660
Those tickets are hard to get.

92
00:06:51,820 --> 00:06:54,140
Since Yue Tangtang is so generous,

93
00:06:54,340 --> 00:06:55,340
you might as well go

94
00:06:55,340 --> 00:06:56,380
and enjoy yourself.

95
00:06:58,900 --> 00:07:00,180
All right then. Thanks.

96
00:07:10,350 --> 00:07:11,311
So it really wasn't you?

97
00:07:12,030 --> 00:07:13,879
Please, like I would waste
my scholarship

98
00:07:13,880 --> 00:07:14,700
on something so dumb.

99
00:07:14,700 --> 00:07:17,480
And I'd never buy a ticket for someone
arrogant, smug, and self-obsessed.

100
00:07:18,860 --> 00:07:19,900
If you hate me that much,

101
00:07:20,580 --> 00:07:22,300
why are you still in the Swimming Club?

102
00:07:22,780 --> 00:07:23,500
Quit then!

103
00:07:25,809 --> 00:07:26,580
Then I'll quit!

104
00:07:43,460 --> 00:07:45,220
Yue Tangtang, you set me up!

105
00:07:45,620 --> 00:07:46,977
What are you talking about?

106
00:07:47,780 --> 00:07:48,780
Quit pretending!

107
00:07:49,060 --> 00:07:50,420
You broke Han Yansheng's trophy

108
00:07:50,420 --> 00:07:52,019
when you tried to give him the ticket.

109
00:07:52,020 --> 00:07:54,390
You were scared he'd find out,
so you skipped the concert.

110
00:07:54,400 --> 00:07:56,590
Then you gave the ticket to me,
so I'd take the fall.

111
00:08:00,900 --> 00:08:01,860
Am I right?

112
00:08:02,220 --> 00:08:04,620
Yue Tangtang,
you gave Jian Dan the ticket

113
00:08:04,620 --> 00:08:05,809
because of that?

114
00:08:06,049 --> 00:08:07,423
I did not!

115
00:08:08,312 --> 00:08:10,580
I gave it to you out of kindness.
How could you accuse me?

116
00:08:11,340 --> 00:08:13,220
And do you even have proof

117
00:08:13,311 --> 00:08:14,688
about that broken trophy?

118
00:08:15,060 --> 00:08:16,300
The ticket Han Yansheng had

119
00:08:16,300 --> 00:08:17,300
is the best proof!

120
00:08:17,823 --> 00:08:19,300
Even if you deny it,

121
00:08:19,488 --> 00:08:20,620
Han Yansheng and I both know

122
00:08:20,620 --> 00:08:21,540
you did it.

123
00:08:22,143 --> 00:08:22,820
Han Yansheng?

124
00:08:24,044 --> 00:08:25,442
Besides the trophy,

125
00:08:25,688 --> 00:08:27,460
you're the one who swapped
my apology letter

126
00:08:27,490 --> 00:08:28,844
for his meme, aren't you?

127
00:08:30,140 --> 00:08:31,494
It wasn't me.

128
00:08:31,860 --> 00:08:32,820
Don't lie.

129
00:08:32,980 --> 00:08:34,797
That day, just Mi Fen, you, and I were

130
00:08:34,858 --> 00:08:35,740
in the dorm.

131
00:08:37,100 --> 00:08:38,500
It's just your theory.

132
00:08:38,580 --> 00:08:39,577
Where's your proof?

133
00:08:39,700 --> 00:08:41,220
That's easy.

134
00:08:41,340 --> 00:08:42,911
There are only a few places on campus

135
00:08:42,933 --> 00:08:43,755
that print photos.

136
00:08:43,844 --> 00:08:44,900
I'll just ask around.

137
00:08:48,220 --> 00:08:49,380
So what if it was me?

138
00:08:49,500 --> 00:08:51,088
This all started because of you.

139
00:08:51,133 --> 00:08:52,666
I wouldn't have quit the Swimming Club

140
00:08:52,666 --> 00:08:53,711
if it weren't for you!

141
00:08:54,180 --> 00:08:56,060
You little pest! You're such a pain!

142
00:08:56,660 --> 00:08:57,980
You don't have to like me.

143
00:08:58,300 --> 00:08:59,700
But you don't get to frame me.

144
00:09:03,380 --> 00:09:04,700
I let the past slide.

145
00:09:06,383 --> 00:09:07,860
But if you come after me again,

146
00:09:08,311 --> 00:09:09,755
don't blame me for fighting back.

147
00:09:09,955 --> 00:09:11,300
Do you think I'm scared of you?

148
00:09:11,420 --> 00:09:12,460
What did you say? I'll...

149
00:09:25,140 --> 00:09:26,860
Jian Dan, where are you going?

150
00:09:27,260 --> 00:09:28,020
To the library.

151
00:09:29,300 --> 00:09:30,420
Aren't you going to the pool?

152
00:09:31,100 --> 00:09:32,300
I'm not going anymore.

153
00:09:59,060 --> 00:10:01,432
Excuse me, can I borrow your phone?

154
00:10:01,660 --> 00:10:02,220
Sure.

155
00:10:02,580 --> 00:10:03,260
Thank you.

156
00:10:12,740 --> 00:10:13,940
Hello, Grandma?

157
00:10:14,807 --> 00:10:17,100
Jian Dan, what's wrong with your phone?

158
00:10:17,941 --> 00:10:19,540
It's off.

159
00:10:19,777 --> 00:10:21,540
Plus, the signal's really bad
in the dorm.

160
00:10:21,540 --> 00:10:22,900
So I miss a lot of calls.

161
00:10:22,977 --> 00:10:24,200
But don't worry, I'm fine.

162
00:10:24,220 --> 00:10:27,180
Are you getting along
with your classmates?

163
00:10:27,771 --> 00:10:30,100
They love the snacks you made.

164
00:10:31,164 --> 00:10:32,620
What about your club activities?

165
00:10:32,940 --> 00:10:33,620
Club activities?

166
00:10:34,858 --> 00:10:36,340
Wow, you know about it?

167
00:10:37,155 --> 00:10:38,740
I joined the Swimming Club.

168
00:10:39,541 --> 00:10:41,540
I'm the fastest girl on the team.

169
00:10:41,580 --> 00:10:42,660
Everyone likes me a lot.

170
00:10:43,814 --> 00:10:45,500
Do you have enough money to spend?

171
00:10:45,700 --> 00:10:46,420
I have enough.

172
00:10:46,740 --> 00:10:48,688
Just take care of yourself, okay?

173
00:10:49,460 --> 00:10:50,060
All right.

174
00:10:50,740 --> 00:10:52,140
I'm still in the library.

175
00:10:52,300 --> 00:10:54,460
So I have to go.
I'll talk to you next time.

176
00:10:54,496 --> 00:10:55,300
Okay.

177
00:10:58,580 --> 00:10:59,340
Thank you.

178
00:11:31,980 --> 00:11:35,820
(Apartment 17)

179
00:13:00,180 --> 00:13:03,620
The number you have dialed
is currently unavailable.

180
00:13:09,380 --> 00:13:11,260
Han, what are you doing?

181
00:13:12,380 --> 00:13:13,577
Did you get a new phone?

182
00:13:16,111 --> 00:13:18,377
Is Yue Tangtang in the same department
as Jian Dan?

183
00:13:19,140 --> 00:13:21,020
Same department and same dorm.

184
00:13:23,260 --> 00:13:24,800
Send me her number.

185
00:13:25,460 --> 00:13:25,980
Now.

186
00:13:26,940 --> 00:13:28,860
Why do you need it?

187
00:13:54,780 --> 00:13:55,340
Who's this?

188
00:13:55,940 --> 00:13:57,460
It's me, Han Yansheng.

189
00:13:59,380 --> 00:14:00,377
Han Yansheng?

190
00:14:02,260 --> 00:14:04,020
Why are you calling me?

191
00:14:04,700 --> 00:14:05,900
Put Jian Dan on.

192
00:14:07,220 --> 00:14:07,780
Jian Dan?

193
00:14:08,900 --> 00:14:09,977
Let her take the call.

194
00:14:10,100 --> 00:14:11,133
I need to talk to her.

195
00:14:13,820 --> 00:14:17,340
Jian Dan, quit pooping
and take this call!

196
00:14:18,300 --> 00:14:18,820
You're...

197
00:14:20,900 --> 00:14:21,420
Who's that?

198
00:14:29,060 --> 00:14:30,666
Write me a Club Withdrawal Application.

199
00:14:30,700 --> 00:14:31,900
Minimum 3,000 words.

200
00:14:32,820 --> 00:14:33,540
What?

201
00:14:34,340 --> 00:14:35,940
A 3,000-word withdrawal letter?

202
00:14:36,060 --> 00:14:37,220
Why don't you go eat dirt...

203
00:14:39,980 --> 00:14:42,180
Jian Dan, what did Han Yansheng want?

204
00:14:43,700 --> 00:14:44,953
I already quit the club,

205
00:14:45,006 --> 00:14:46,420
and now he wants a 3,000-word essay?

206
00:14:46,900 --> 00:14:48,793
Is he crazy?

207
00:14:48,866 --> 00:14:49,820
When you go talk to him,

208
00:14:49,820 --> 00:14:50,580
I'll come with you.

209
00:14:53,300 --> 00:14:54,222
Give it back to me.

210
00:14:54,900 --> 00:14:56,540
Why did he call me to find you?

211
00:14:57,860 --> 00:14:59,500
A 3,000-word withdrawal letter...

212
00:14:59,911 --> 00:15:01,488
How am I even supposed to write that?

213
00:15:20,244 --> 00:15:22,333
Here is the 3,000-word
withdrawal letter you wanted.

214
00:15:22,377 --> 00:15:23,600
Not one more, not one less.

215
00:15:24,100 --> 00:15:26,060
Not good enough. Rewrite it.

216
00:15:26,866 --> 00:15:29,577
How can you say it's not good enough
when you didn't even read it?

217
00:15:29,800 --> 00:15:31,288
I have the final say.

218
00:15:31,711 --> 00:15:32,820
You're not officially out

219
00:15:32,900 --> 00:15:34,140
until it's approved.

220
00:15:34,420 --> 00:15:34,900
You...

221
00:15:37,860 --> 00:15:39,700
Approved or not,

222
00:15:39,800 --> 00:15:41,790
(Club Withdrawal Application)
I'm not coming back.

223
00:15:41,860 --> 00:15:42,777
Stop right there!

224
00:15:48,260 --> 00:15:49,820
Is there anything else?

225
00:15:54,460 --> 00:15:55,020
For you.

226
00:15:57,060 --> 00:15:58,422
Why are you giving me a phone?

227
00:15:58,940 --> 00:16:00,420
I broke yours the other day.

228
00:16:00,900 --> 00:16:02,100
Take this one for now.

229
00:16:03,740 --> 00:16:04,300
No, thanks.

230
00:16:04,860 --> 00:16:07,540
Do you still want
to keep dragging this out with me?

231
00:16:08,333 --> 00:16:10,288
Who said I want anything to do with you?

232
00:16:11,266 --> 00:16:12,780
Or do you just want a new phone?

233
00:16:17,620 --> 00:16:19,000
Fine. I'll use it for now.

234
00:16:19,380 --> 00:16:20,977
But I will pay you back gradually.

235
00:17:09,980 --> 00:17:12,581
♪The wind blows through her curly hair♪

236
00:17:12,590 --> 00:17:14,967
♪And her sweet cheeks♪

237
00:17:16,310 --> 00:17:19,004
♪She accepts youth as a cryptic syntax♪

238
00:17:19,032 --> 00:17:21,428
♪And expresses it with sincerity♪

239
00:17:21,748 --> 00:17:27,856
♪Growing up, she's a stubborn flower♪

240
00:17:28,170 --> 00:17:34,628
♪Was she afraid?
She once asked herself that too♪

241
00:17:34,780 --> 00:17:40,985
♪Hypatia, that passionate
version of her♪

242
00:17:41,030 --> 00:17:47,258
♪Dazzling like midsummer,
melting sorrow♪

243
00:17:47,340 --> 00:17:53,602
♪Hypatia, that radiant version of her♪

244
00:17:53,630 --> 00:18:00,129
♪If love is complicated,
she answers with a smile♪

245
00:18:00,230 --> 00:18:06,581
♪Hypatia, that passionate
version of her♪

246
00:18:06,590 --> 00:18:12,858
♪Dazzling like midsummer,
melting sorrow♪

247
00:18:12,970 --> 00:18:19,395
♪Hypatia, that radiant version of her♪

248
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:25,752
♪If love is complicated,
she answers with a smile♪

249
00:18:45,280 --> 00:18:47,180
Jian Dan, let's eat. I'm starving.

250
00:19:19,900 --> 00:19:20,700
Break time!

251
00:19:22,500 --> 00:19:23,580
Han, have a drink.

252
00:19:27,300 --> 00:19:29,660
Something feels missing
without Jian Dan around.

253
00:19:34,020 --> 00:19:34,700
I'm off to class.

254
00:19:35,580 --> 00:19:37,420
I'll leave the rest
of the training to you.

255
00:19:38,133 --> 00:19:39,400
Hey, Han, you can't just...

256
00:19:43,140 --> 00:19:44,820
Han is cold-blooded.

257
00:19:53,432 --> 00:19:55,540
(Gu Entong:
Shi, I'm coming back.)

258
00:20:03,540 --> 00:20:05,740
Electives start next week.

259
00:20:05,740 --> 00:20:07,820
Mi Fen, what class did you sign up for?

260
00:20:08,540 --> 00:20:09,860
Film Appreciation.

261
00:20:10,260 --> 00:20:12,460
We only watch movies,

262
00:20:12,460 --> 00:20:14,190
write a few reflections,
and take no exams.

263
00:20:14,220 --> 00:20:15,380
Pretty smart, right?

264
00:20:16,940 --> 00:20:17,900
What did you pick?

265
00:20:18,820 --> 00:20:19,860
Applied Math.

266
00:20:20,860 --> 00:20:22,740
What? You picked Applied Math?

267
00:20:24,833 --> 00:20:26,173
It has high credit hours.

268
00:20:26,246 --> 00:20:27,213
I know that.

269
00:20:27,266 --> 00:20:28,540
But haven't you heard?

270
00:20:28,620 --> 00:20:31,260
Professor Wang teaches that course.
He's a total nightmare.

271
00:20:31,280 --> 00:20:33,444
He has the highest fail rate
in the whole university.

272
00:20:33,466 --> 00:20:35,060
Every year, he fails so many students

273
00:20:35,060 --> 00:20:36,460
who took his classes.

274
00:20:36,900 --> 00:20:37,860
Is it really that bad?

